Crypt::RIPEMD160 - Perl extension for the RIPEMD-160 Hash function

SYNOPSIS

    use Crypt::RIPEMD160;

    my $hasher = Crypt::RIPEMD160->new;
    $hasher->add("some data");
    my $digest = $hasher->digest();      # 20-byte binary
    my $hex    = $hasher->hexdigest();   # human-readable hex

    # One-shot convenience
    my $digest = Crypt::RIPEMD160->hash("data");
    my $hex    = Crypt::RIPEMD160->hexhash("data");

    # HMAC-RIPEMD-160 (RFC 2104)
    use Crypt::RIPEMD160::MAC;
    my $mac = Crypt::RIPEMD160::MAC->new($key);
    $mac->add("data");
    my $auth = $mac->mac();

DESCRIPTION

Crypt::RIPEMD160 provides a Perl interface to the RIPEMD-160 message
digest algorithm via an XS wrapper around the reference C implementation
by Antoon Bosselaers (ESAT-COSIC, Katholieke Universiteit Leuven).

Crypt::RIPEMD160::MAC implements HMAC-RIPEMD-160 as described in
RFC 2104, using Crypt::RIPEMD160 as the underlying hash.

INSTALLATION

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install

REQUIREMENTS

    Perl 5.10 or later
    A C compiler (for the XS extension)

SOURCE

    https://github.com/cpan-authors/Crypt-RIPEMD160

BUGS

    https://github.com/cpan-authors/Crypt-RIPEMD160/issues

REFERENCES

The RIPEMD-160 algorithm is published in "Fast Software Encryption,
LNCS 1039, D. Gollmann (Ed.), pp.71-82".

HMAC test vectors are from RFC 2286.

